              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "If we're going full OCD, it's \"LEGO\" all caps.  "
              },
              {
                "type": "emoji",
                "name": "nerd_face"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "  And the pieces are called \"LEGO bricks,\" which is, of course, ambiguous as a brick is also category of piece among others: plates, tiles, slopes, beams, pins, etc.\n\nStudio is my preferred CAD "
              },
              {
                "type": "link",
                "url": "https://www.bricklink.com/v3/studio/download.page"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " as it makes generating plans from models relatively easy.\n\nFor a simulator, I don't know but would love to find out.  I'm going to take a look at MecaBricks."
              }
            ]
